# Line endings are part of "canonical everything": the tree is LF in the index
# and LF in every working tree, on every platform.
#
# Without this, a Windows checkout with the default core.autocrlf=true (what
# GitHub's windows-latest runner uses) converts every file to CRLF, and gofmt
# then reports the entire repository as unformatted. It would also desynchronize
# the web/dist freshness test, which compares committed bytes.
#
# Every tracked file is text today; add explicit `binary` entries here if that
# ever stops being true.
* text=auto eol=lf
